    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "My workflow is typically to get things working with a Goerli chain on my laptop (running macOs), and then to test it out on a couple linux nodes.  I can migrate to using a linux build server/VM/container for that second part, but had been using the Makefile's xgo support up until now since it seemed the most straight-forward/discoverable way to do cross-platform builds.\r\n\r\nMaybe we should add a note to the Cross Compilation targets that they aren't the preferred way to build, and that for best results you should use the build system on the target OS whenever possible?",
